nsitive_key` hard-codes `\"branch\"`, `\"cwd\"`, `\"path\"`, `\"worktree\"`, `\"uuid\"` and `*Branch`/`*-branch` suffixes. These are agentlog/GitButler-domain field names, not generic secrets, so redaction is no longer \"only redaction\" — it encodes which transcript/environment fields are sensitive. Suggested fix: pass the sensitive-key policy in from the capture/write layer (or a const list owned there), keeping `redaction.rs` to the entropy/named-secret mechanics.\n\n**P2 — Preview/truncation logic is duplicated across four sites.** Char-window-with-ellipsis truncation appears in `cli.rs:409-419` (`display_preview`, 120), `skim.rs:283-303` (`short_line` 120 / `preview_text` 320), and `outline_support.rs:19-27` (`compact_preview`, 320). `push_unique` is also copy-pasted in `session_outline.rs:146` and `timeline_outline.rs:299`. Suggested fix: one shared truncation helper parameterized by length, and a single `push_unique`.\n\n**P2 — `skim.rs:213-262` semantic labeling lives in the output layer.** `turn_labels` infers milestones (\"implemented\", \"tested\", etc.) from preview text inside the Display-oriented skim module. This is content analysis, not formatting; it belongs nearer the read/outline layer that produces `TimelineTurnOutline`. Low urgency since skim is the only consumer, but it mixes interpretation into a serialization module.\n\n**Clean (no action):** `transcript.rs` correctly has zero GitMeta knowledge; `capture.rs` is a thin orchestrator; `cli.rs` resolves `workdir` before business logic in every arm; read-side modules share parsing via `read_support.rs` rather than duplicating it; output types (`SkimReport`, `SessionTimeline`, `SessionRecords`) live with their producers and `CommandOutput`'s Display stays in `cli.rs`.\nagentId: a78a12465dba348cd (use SendMessage with to: 'a78a12465dba348cd' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 104015\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 41576</usage>","tool_name":"Agent","tool_input":null,"source_record":{"parentU